{"word":"ἀναύδητος","slug":"ἀναύδητος","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>ἀναύδητος</b></el> <br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:αὐδάω'><el>αὐδάω</el></a>\n<p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>not to be spoken, unutterable, ineffable</i>, <a href='S:Latin'>Lat.</a> <el>infandus</el>, <b><a href='S:Aeschylus'>Aesch.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b><i>unspoken, impossible</i>, <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><i>speechless</i>, <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}